---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="WellPeps' commitment to digital accessibility and how to reach us if you encounter a barrier."
>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Read first — the statement is only as good as the audit behind it</strong>
    <p>
      An accessibility statement is a factual representation. Before this page goes live, WellPeps
      must commission a WCAG 2.1 AA evaluation (automated scan plus a manual keyboard and
      screen-reader pass at minimum) — the conformance wording in Section 2 depends entirely on that
      outcome.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="legal__meta">
    Statement Date: <span class="ph">[CLIENT: date first published]</span><br />
    Last Reviewed: <span class="ph">[CLIENT: same as statement date for v1]</span>
  </p>

  <h2>1. Our Commitment</h2>
  <p>
    WellPeps is committed to making our website and services accessible to everyone, including
    people with disabilities. We believe access to telehealth information and care should not depend
    on ability, and we work to provide an experience that is perceivable, operable, understandable,
    and robust for all visitors.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Conformance Status</h2>
  <p>
    The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) define requirements to improve accessibility for
    people with disabilities, at three levels of conformance: A, AA, and AAA.
  </p>
  <p>
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT/VENDOR: choose one based on the audit outcome — do not publish the stronger claim without evidence]</span>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Option A</strong> (only if a completed audit supports it): &ldquo;This website is
      fully conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Option B</strong> (the honest default for most sites at launch): &ldquo;This website
      is partially conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA, meaning some parts of the content do not yet
      fully conform. We are actively working to achieve full conformance.&rdquo;
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Measures We Take</h2>
  <p>
    WellPeps takes the following measures to support accessibility:
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: keep only the items that are actually true — each is a factual claim]</span>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Include accessibility in our design and development standards for all new pages;</li>
    <li>
      Test with automated tools (<span class="ph">[CLIENT: e.g., axe, Lighthouse, WAVE]</span>) and
      manual keyboard and screen-reader review
      (<span class="ph">[CLIENT: which screen readers — NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver]</span>);
    </li>
    <li>
      Maintain semantic HTML, sufficient color contrast, visible focus states, and support for
      reduced-motion preferences;
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="ph">[CLIENT: if applicable]</span> Engage an external accessibility vendor
      (<span class="ph">[CLIENT: vendor name]</span>) for periodic evaluation;
    </li>
    <li>
      Train our design and engineering team on accessible development practices.
      <span class="ph">[CLIENT: confirm or delete]</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Compatibility</h2>
  <p>
    This website is designed to be compatible with recent versions of major browsers (Chrome,
    Firefox, Safari, Edge) and with common assistive technologies, including screen readers and
    screen-magnification software, on desktop and mobile.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Known Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    Despite our efforts, some content may not yet be fully accessible. Known limitations as of the
    statement date:
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT/VENDOR: populate from the audit findings with a fix timeline for each; if the audit finds none, state &ldquo;No known limitations at this time.&rdquo;]</span>
  </p>

  <h2>6. Alternative Access</h2>
  <p>
    If any part of this website is difficult to use, you can complete every step of the WellPeps
    process — including consultations, ordering, and account changes — by phone with our support
    team at <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a> (Mon–Fri, 9am–6pm ET).
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: confirm phone support genuinely covers the full signup-to-refill journey; if any step is web-only, either fix that or narrow this sentence]</span>
  </p>

  <h2>7. Feedback and Contact</h2>
  <p>
    We welcome feedback on the accessibility of this website. If you encounter an accessibility
    barrier, please contact us:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Email:
      <span class="ph">[CLIENT: dedicated monitored address — accessibility@wellpeps.com recommended]</span>
    </li>
    <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a></li>
    <li><span class="ph">[CLIENT: postal address for formal correspondence]</span></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: e.g., 3 business days]</span> and to propose a resolution or
    accessible alternative within <span class="ph">[CLIENT: e.g., 10 business days]</span>. This
    statement is reviewed and updated
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: cadence — annually at minimum, and after any major redesign]</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Enforcement and Formal Complaints</h2>
  <p>
    If you are not satisfied with our response, you may escalate your concern to
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: internal escalation contact/title]</span>. U.S. users may also contact
    the U.S. Department of Justice regarding ADA concerns.
    <span class="ph">[COUNSEL: confirm whether to keep the DOJ reference — included here as the transparent default]</span>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
